<subSubSection id="C30FB2903524FFE8FF47FE61FDD7FDE6" pageId="7" pageNumber="363" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BAAE11B3524FFE8FF47FE61FDD7FDE6" blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis id="B9613D093524FFE8FF47FE61FEE1FE51" bold="true" box="[199,334,403,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet comes from the 
<typeStatus id="54AE5FB93524FFE8FD6FFE66FCB0FE52" box="[751,799,404,430]" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">type</typeStatus>
locality, near the Tequendama waterfall, one of the most important sacred places in the Muisca civilization, a Chibcha-speaking indigenous people who inhabit the central highlands of the eastern Andes in 
<collectingCountry id="F302A18B3524FFE8FD92FE29FD2BFE09" box="[530,644,475,501]" name="Colombia" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. To be treated as an arbitrary combination of letters, and hence without the need to agree in gender with the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30FB2903524FFE8FF47FDD1FD9FFD56" pageId="7" pageNumber="363" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAAE11B3524FFE8FF47FDD1FD9FFD56" blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis id="B9613D093524FFE8FF47FDD1FEEDFDC1" bold="true" box="[199,322,547,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C159A983524FFE8FE3BFDD6FDCAFDC1" authority="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez, 2022" authorityName="Muñoz-Charry &amp; Galvis &amp; Martínez" authorityYear="2022" box="[443,613,547,573]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Lapsias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tequendama" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9613D093524FFE8FE3BFDD6FDCAFDC1" box="[443,613,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">L. tequendama</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9613D093524FFE8FDEFFDD1FD63FDC1" bold="true" box="[623,716,547,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25280723524FFE8FDEFFDD1FD63FDC1" box="[623,716,547,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="363" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be recognized from those of the remaining species in the genus by their longer and stronger embolus (e), with several bumps/apophyses on it, a long median apophysis (ma), a prolateral long and pointed accessory tegular apophysis (pTa) and the retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA) curved and projected outward (
<figureCitation id="132EFD9E3524FFE8FE20FD7DFD8CFD56" box="[416,547,655,682]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[151,1412,892,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-403@6.[151,1436,885,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–26. L. tequedama sp. nov., male holotype (ICN-Ar 8268), 20 habitus; 21, 24 left palp, ventral view; 22, 25 same, retrolateral view; 23 same, dorsal view; 26 same, prolateral view. Abbreviations: e=embolus, ma=median apophysis, pTa=prolateral tegular apophysis, RTA=retrolateral tibial apophysis, sd=sperm duct. Scale bars = 2.0 mm (20), 0.5 mm (21– 26)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501136/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">Figs 21–26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30FB2903524FFE8FF47FD41FE0DFB81" pageId="7" pageNumber="363" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAAE11B3524FFE8FF47FD41FB29FBC9" blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis id="B9613D093524FFE8FF47FD41FD88FD31" bold="true" box="[199,551,691,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">
Description. Male (
<typeStatus id="54AE5FB93524FFE8FE2EFD41FDB5FD31" box="[430,538,691,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">holotype</typeStatus>
).
</emphasis>
Total length: 5.40. Carapace brown with a medial yellow arrow-shaped mark and two yellow posterolateral lines, 2.52 long, 1.95 wide, 1.58 high (
<figureCitation id="132EFD9E3524FFE8FC3CFD25FBBBFD0D" box="[956,1044,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[151,1412,892,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-403@6.[151,1436,885,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–26. L. tequedama sp. nov., male holotype (ICN-Ar 8268), 20 habitus; 21, 24 left palp, ventral view; 22, 25 same, retrolateral view; 23 same, dorsal view; 26 same, prolateral view. Abbreviations: e=embolus, ma=median apophysis, pTa=prolateral tegular apophysis, RTA=retrolateral tibial apophysis, sd=sperm duct. Scale bars = 2.0 mm (20), 0.5 mm (21– 26)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501136/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). OC brown-reddish with eyes on black marks, 1.13 long. Anterior eye row 1.73 wide and posterior 1.73 wide. Sternum yellowish, 1.08 long, 0.94 wide. Labium yellowish, 0.48 long, 0.41 wide. Chelicerae brown, with two retromarginal and three promarginal teeth. Palp brown-yellowish, with thick embolus (e) that emerge wide in base and has several irregularities along accompanying by a knife-like accessory tegular apophysis (pTa), hook-like median apophysis (ma) surrounded by membranous tissue, the retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA) curved and projected ventral (
<figureCitation id="132EFD9E3524FFE8FBF5FC79FB58FC5A" box="[1141,1271,907,934]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[151,1412,892,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-403@6.[151,1436,885,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–26. L. tequedama sp. nov., male holotype (ICN-Ar 8268), 20 habitus; 21, 24 left palp, ventral view; 22, 25 same, retrolateral view; 23 same, dorsal view; 26 same, prolateral view. Abbreviations: e=embolus, ma=median apophysis, pTa=prolateral tegular apophysis, RTA=retrolateral tibial apophysis, sd=sperm duct. Scale bars = 2.0 mm (20), 0.5 mm (21– 26)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501136/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">Figs 21–26</figureCitation>
). Leg formula: 4132, all yellow with black marks. Leg macrosetae: femur, I p 1 di, d 1 di; II–IV p 1 di, d 2 di; patella, I–II p 1 me; III– IV p 1 me, r 1 me; tibia, I v 2–2–2, p 1–0–1; II v 1–2–2, p 1–0–1; III v 2–0–2, p 1–0–1, r 1–0–1; IV v 1–0–2, p 1–0–1, r 1–0–1; metatarsus, I v 2–2, p 1–1; II v 2–2, p 1–1, r 1 –1; III–IV v 1–1–1, p 1–1–2, r 1–1–2. Abdomen light yellow with an anteromedial dark brown spot and posteromedial chevron marks (
<figureCitation id="132EFD9E3524FFE8FBA5FBE9FBD6FBC9" box="[1061,1145,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1908,1932]" captionTargetBox="[151,1412,892,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-403@6.[151,1436,885,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–26. L. tequedama sp. nov., male holotype (ICN-Ar 8268), 20 habitus; 21, 24 left palp, ventral view; 22, 25 same, retrolateral view; 23 same, dorsal view; 26 same, prolateral view. Abbreviations: e=embolus, ma=median apophysis, pTa=prolateral tegular apophysis, RTA=retrolateral tibial apophysis, sd=sperm duct. Scale bars = 2.0 mm (20), 0.5 mm (21– 26)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501136/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAAE11B3524FFE8FF47FBCDFBBDFBA6" blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1257]" box="[199,1042,1087,1114]" pageId="7" pageNumber="363">
